<item>
            <title>[LANG-1710] ReflectionToStringBuilder changes in version 3.13.0 has broken the logic for overriding classes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-1710</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is said that overriding classes should overload two methods:&#160; &lt;em&gt;#getValue(java.lang.reflect.Field)}&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;#accept(java.lang.reflect.Field)}&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But since 3.13.0 getValue(java.lang.reflect.Field)} no longer called in&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;em&gt;appendFieldsIn&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;System.out.println(&quot;An object: &quot; + ReflectionToStringBuilder.toString(anObject));&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A subclass can control field output by overriding the methods:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;{@link #accept(java.lang.reflect.Field)}&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;{@link #getValue(java.lang.reflect.Field)}&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Also consider to use &lt;em&gt;trySetAccessible&lt;/em&gt; instead of&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;em&gt;AccessibleObject.setAccessible(fields, true);&lt;/em&gt; and skip not accessible fields.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
